rbnIcrMIB.name: rbnIcrMIB
rbnIcrMIB.contactinfo: Ericsson, Inc. Postal: 100 Headquarters Drive San Jose, CA 95134-1370 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599
rbnIcrMIB.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing Inter Chassis Resilience(ICR).

rbnIcrTable.name: rbnIcrTable
rbnIcrTable.description: This table consists of ICR management objects.

rbnIcrEntry.name: rbnIcrEntry
rbnIcrEntry.description: Each entry contains management objects of an ICR node.

rbnIcrId.name: rbnIcrId
rbnIcrId.description: The unique identifier of the ICR node.

rbnIcrLocalAddressType.name: rbnIcrLocalAddressType
rbnIcrLocalAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of 'rbnIcrLocalAddress'.

rbnIcrLocalAddress.name: rbnIcrLocalAddress
rbnIcrLocalAddress.description: This object indicates the local address used to send/receive ICR messages. The type of the address is determined by the corresponding 'rbnIcrLocalAddressType'.

rbnIcrLocalPort.name: rbnIcrLocalPort
rbnIcrLocalPort.description: This object indicates the local port number used to send/receive ICR messages.

rbnIcrPeerAddressType.name: rbnIcrPeerAddressType
rbnIcrPeerAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of 'rbnIcrPeerAddress'.

rbnIcrPeerAddress.name: rbnIcrPeerAddress
rbnIcrPeerAddress.description: This object indicates the address used by the peer ICR node to send/receive ICR messages. The type of the address is determined by the corresponding 'rbnIcrPeerAddressType'.

rbnIcrPeerPort.name: rbnIcrPeerPort
rbnIcrPeerPort.description: This object indicates the port number used by the peer ICR node to send/receive ICR messages.

rbnIcrPriority.name: rbnIcrPriority
rbnIcrPriority.description: This object indicates the ICR priority. The priority is used for setting the initial preference level when the prefixes are advertised and is used for tie-break in case both the local ICR node and its peer node are booted up at the same time. The local and the peer ICR nodes MUST configure different priorities

rbnIcrKeepAliveInterval.name: rbnIcrKeepAliveInterval
rbnIcrKeepAliveInterval.description: This object indicates the interval that the node sends ICR keep alive messages to its peer node.

rbnIcrHoldTime.name: rbnIcrHoldTime
rbnIcrHoldTime.description: This object indicates the time, after which, if the node has not received a ICR keep alive message from its peer node, it declares the peer loss.

rbnIcrState.name: rbnIcrState
rbnIcrState.description: The current ICR state: - 'initialize', which indicates that the node is in the process of deciding its role(active or standby). - 'active', which indicates that the node operates as ICR active node. - 'standby', which indicates that the node operates as ICR standby node. - 'pendingStandby', which indicates that the node(previously in 'active' state) is waiting for operator intervention to transit to 'standby' state after ICR switchover.

rbnIcrAdminStatus.name: rbnIcrAdminStatus
rbnIcrAdminStatus.description: This object controls ICR node. Setting this object to 'up' will enable the ICR node. The node will transition from 'initialize' state to 'active' or 'standby' state depending on the value of 'rbnIcrPriority'. Setting this object to 'down' will disable the ICR node. The node will transition from its current state to 'initialize'. To modify other 'read-create' objects in the conceptual row, the 'rbnIcrAdminStatus' object must be set to 'down'. The value of the 'rbnIcrRowStatus' object must be 'active' in order for this object to be set to 'up'.

rbnIcrRowStatus.name: rbnIcrRowStatus
rbnIcrRowStatus.description: The object is used to create and delete 'rbnIcrEntry' conceptual rows. Except 'rbnIcrAdminStatus', 'read-create' objects in the conceptual row cannot be modified when rbnIcrRowStatus is set to active(1). To change 'rbnIcrRowStatus' from 'active' to a different value, the 'rbnIcrAdminStatus' object must be 'down'. To create a row in this table, 'rbnIcrRowStatus' could be set to either 'createAndGo(4)' or 'createAndWait(5)'. Until all objects in the conceptual row are appropriately configured, 'rbnIcrRowStatus' will transit to 'notReady(3)'.

rbnIcrInconsistencyError.name: rbnIcrInconsistencyError
rbnIcrInconsistencyError.description: This object indicates the ICR inconsistency error code.

rbnIcrNewActive.name: rbnIcrNewActive
rbnIcrNewActive.description: This notification is sent when the state of the ICR node has changed to active.

rbnIcrNewStandby.name: rbnIcrNewStandby
rbnIcrNewStandby.description: This notification is sent when the state of the ICR node has changed to standby.

rbnIcrNewPendingStandby.name: rbnIcrNewPendingStandby
rbnIcrNewPendingStandby.description: This notification is sent when the state of the ICR node has changed to pendingStandby.

rbnIcrInconsistency.name: rbnIcrInconsistency
rbnIcrInconsistency.description: This notification is sent when an ICR inconsistency error is encountered.

rbnIcrMIBCompliance.name: rbnIcrMIBCompliance
rbnIcrMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for ICR MIB implementations.

rbnIcrNotificationObjectGroup.name: rbnIcrNotificationObjectGroup
rbnIcrNotificationObjectGroup.description: Conformance group for objects contained in ICR notifications.
